/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/building_models/current_hunts/big-thinkers/codex-atlas/execution/instances/yang-mills/strategies/strategy-001/explorations/exploration-009/REPORT.md:343:The 't Hooft area law was proved for N → ∞. For N = ∞ to help with N = 2 or N = 3, one needs rigorous 1/N corrections. The master loop equations (Makeenko-Migdal) provide a systematic 1/N expansion, and these have been analyzed by Chatterjee-Jafarov (2016). The key step missing: showing the 1/N expansion converges (not just is asymptotic) for the mass gap. This seems very hard but is at least a precisely defined problem.
