el-set distribution tails IC-dependent (TG p~10, Random p~8-9, ABC p~2.1 < 10/3); Chebyshev tightness ratios ~3-5x and k-independent (constant slack, not beta-improving). S2-E005: Frequency-localized De Giorgi via LP decomposition CLOSED — Bernstein exchange rate 2^{3j/5} is dimensional, CZ is optimal frequency-by-frequency estimate, LP gives 5-10x worse bounds; paraproduct transition (resonance at low k, paraproduct at high k); direction 2 closed. S2-E006: Non-CZ pressure routes (IBP beta=1, H^1/BMO beta=4/3, CRW beta<=1) — beta=4/3 TOOL-INDEPENDENT, locked to NS quadratic structure; CZ consolidation gain exactly 1/3; 12 published approaches surveyed, none beat 4/3; 3 remaining directions. S2-E007: Adversarial review confirms obstruction — all 7 closures survive attack, 3 combination attacks fail, 15-paper lit search + Vasseur 2025 confirms no improvement, Tao 2016 supercritical connection; novel claim rankings (Claim 3 seven-route obstruction most significant); SDP formalization top priority. S2-E008: Chebyshev bound PROVABLY TIGHT for div-free fields — constant field u=(c,0,0) achieves ratio->1; all 4 De Giorgi chain steps individually tight; beta = 4/3 SHARP (rigorous); div-free level-set question RESOLVED (no improvement); SDP unnecessary.** **28 entries.**
